title: atish presents Afterhour Sounds Podcast Nr. 134
description:
© artwork by franz zünkler ➲ contact ✉ franz.zuenkler@t-online.de

Atish (https://soundcloud.com/atish) presents Afterhour Sounds Podcast Nr.134

Unsere Nr. 134 kommt heute von einem amerikanischen Künstler, der mich seit 3 Jahren ununterbrochen musikalisch begleitet. Ich erinnere mich noch sehr gut an seine damalige Bunring Man Aufnahme… Sie haute mich schlichtweg um. Seitdem komme ich nicht mehr um Ihn herum. 

Die Rede ist von „Atish“, einem ehrlichen und unkomplizierten Künstler, der keinen geradlinigen Weg ging. Anfangs noch Programmierer für Facebook, entschied er sich vor knapp 10 Jahren selber Musik zu mixen, wie seine unzähligen Mixe belegen. Anders als viele andere Künstler, die gerne ihre so genannte ‚peinliche‘ Anfangszeit verheimlichen möchten, sind bei Ihm tatsächlich noch alle Mixe zum Anhören verfügbar. Dass er damals wie heute seinem Sound gleich geblieben ist, spricht umso mehr für diesen sympathischen Menschen. 

Sein Coming Out hatte er 2012, als er auf dem Robot Heart art-car spielte. Seitdem ging es steil bergauf. Tokio, New York, Istanbul, Berlin,…um nur einige Stationen seines vollgepackten Kalenders zu nennen.

Aber auch in seiner Wahlstadt San Francisco treibt er weiterhin sein Unwesen. Und wie!!! Neben dem etwas anderen Clubformat mit dem Namen ‚Late night tonight!‘, einer Mischung aus Talk-Show und Club Party, gründete er auch das Label ‚Manjumasi‘. 
Und wäre dies nicht schon genug, feilt er in jeder freien Minute an kommenden Releases und Remixen. Tendenz steigend. Sowohl in Qualität, als auch in Quantität. Wir sind gespannt.

Das von Ihm eingespielte Set ist eine herrlich ‚afterhoureske‘ Reise ins Dickicht der melodischen und verträumten elektronischen Musik. Das sich Atish für dieses Set etwas ganz besonderes einfallen lassen hat ist unüberhörbar. Ich war beim ersten Hören des Sets tatsächlich komplett geflasht, hatte ich doch etwas anderes erwartet. Aber diese Überraschungsmomente, die unsere Reihe und die jeweiligen musikalischen Interpretationen immer wieder mit sich bringen, hauen mich, nein uns, immer wieder um. Darauf darf man auch ein wenig Stolz sein. Vor allem wenn man am Ende ein ganz außergewöhnliches Set erhält. So auch hier. Schnallt euch an… Ich kann mich nur wiederholen, aber es erwartet euch eine Reise durch verspielte, sehr deepe und hypnothische Felder, wie gemacht für eine tanzbare Afterhour sind. Das gabs bei uns schon lange nicht mehr….seid gespannt.

Wir danken Dir vielmals für dieses besondere Set Atish. Umwerfend und überraschend gut. Wenn Unikat, dann Hier. Chapeu.

Wir sind entzückt.

✘ Atish (San Francisco/United States Of America)

title: Minor Wheel Vol. I
description:
MelleM here, and Hello World! It’s been a long time in the making…but I’m happy to announce that I finally completed my VERY FIRST DJ SET!! :) I give you the Minor Wheel Vol. I.

The overall theme for this set presented itself to me in early 2017, and for the music geeks out there, the Minor Wheel series is an exploration of the beloved Camelot Wheel. For Vol. I, I start at G Minor / 6A…and loop completely around the wheel (minor keys only). You will hear anywhere from 2-4 tracks per key, ending back at G Minor where I started. There is absolutely no skipping of keys along the wheel, and no major keys are used. 

It’s been quite an ambitious and loopy journey making the Minor Wheel Vol. I (pardon the pun). I’ve poured a ton of passion, knowledge, time, and even moments of obsession getting my debut set to a point where I was happy releasing it. It’s an incredibly emotional and magical set for me. Deep, lush, lyrical, evocative, and even a bit melancholic at times…with just enough mistakes here and there for my DJ friends to notice. This takes training wheels to a whole other level. ;)

Thanks for listening. Enjoy, and I welcome all comments and feedback!

title: Global Transmission // Ep 025 II Resident: Loquai (Germany)
description:
// Episode 025:

Konstantin, better known as LoQuai, showcases his talent and dedication for the music through his exceptional productions and careful music selections. Growing up in Germany, Konstantin started really diving into the music in 1998. His combination of psychedelic, trance, breaks, and drum & bass elements combined to create true a progressive sound. Since his first release in 2005, he has released original tracks and remixes on over 70 labels, with many of the tracks released under Mystique Music.

After several busy years deep in creating new music, LoQuai have launching the new show “Unison” on Frisky Radio. With his experience combining multiple elements to become one creative masterpiece, LoQuai’s Unison will truly live up to its name. The best music, carefully and passionately entwined to create one amazing experience.

Check out more from LoQuai at:

// About Us:

Global Transmission is a collaborative project between eight likeminded individuals from around the world who have come together to share their love of electronic music. In a monthly podcast, we deliver a mix of the absolute best in progressive, house and techno. With a combined 100+ years of musical experience across a diverse range of backgrounds, scenes and sounds thousands of miles apart are fused into one cohesive, auditory delight.

With occasional guest mixes highlighting other outstanding local and international artists, Global Transmission strives to be a quality forum for consistently bringing the best of soulful, underground and intelligent dance music to the ears of our listeners the world over.

We hope you enjoy ☺

title: Aenera - San Diego | Mikimau Podcast 091
description:
This weeks special guest embodies the idea of pure expressionism through music. 
Richard “Aenera” Hosea is one of the San Diego locals that’s silently moving and shaping the underground scene in Southern California. To experience a set from Aenera is to experience an eclectic journey through a range of rhythmic, tribal and progressive chakra energy.

Here are his own words to describe the mix...

"There is a common thread, a subtle string that binds us together and music is one vehicle that can take us from one emotion to another. Like traversing the sands of the deep playa at night, new experiences push and pull of us at every turn, enticing us to dive head first into the unknown. The journey is what matters, not the destination. 
This is the intention, the storyline, the ethos of this mix."

 - Aenera

title: Permeate 07
description:
Permeate ~ to pass into or through every part of, to penetrate through the pores, interstices; to be diffused through; pervade; saturate...

Just because my path is different doesn't mean I am lost. If anything, it means that I'm moving on a path that pulls me more than any other. This path is mine and mine alone. Others may walk it with me, but no one can walk it for me. This particular session has been very therapeutic. Its been a time of reflection and refocusing. Receding into my little world has always been necessary, especially being in tune with the vibrations and energy around me. Its all a balancing act taken one day at a time.

The key to this series isn't about perfection but to be in the moment, organically creating what is felt deep inside. The sounds and rhythms, weaving through layers and textures, moving with purpose, seeping into every crevice and pore within oneself. This is the intention and the focus, the spiritual side of the music, which my heart and soul yearns to share with you. Hope you enjoy and thank you for listening. <3

description:
Someone had to provide the 10am(ish) kick off for the Rhythm Society's first experimental All Day Dance Celebration. Turned out that someone was me!

The brief was "deep house", but it's hard to keep me out of the deep end of the Progressive pool, and there's a peak which wanders into Tech House for a while, because genres are fluid and too much of the same thing is dull.

title: atish - [070] - august 2017 - mused and bemused
description:
These last few months, I've spent a fair amount of time musing over my own artistic identity and my place within the bigger space. 

What does it meant to be a "deep house DJ"..."progressive DJ"..."tech-house DJ"..."Burner DJ" [cringe]...and so on?
Does it even matter? Artistically, no, not in the slightest.

But practically, I've come to believe that it does, evidenced by the constrained expectations and sometimes bemusement of promoters who book me.

Unfortunately, being perceived and labeled on a singular dimension isn't such a great thing.
But the good news is that the solution is to just keep doing what I love to do: releasing mixes that weave in and out of moods and feelings, taking you to a destination hopefully different than where you started.

Hope you enjoy the ride...

title: Simon Mark @ Frolic Campout 2017 - Sunday AM Poolside
description:
You are in a campground somewhere near Ukiah with about 150 people. People who danced until 2am on Friday, and (some of them, at least) all the way through until sunrise on Saturday night.

Your mission, should you choose to accept it: wake them up gently around 10:30am. They've all got to pack up their tents, grab a bit of brunch by the pool, and hit the road before 2pm for the long drive home. You want to leave them mildly energized, but not feeling like they were put through the wringer.

My answer to this conundrum: start with some super-dreamy sounds and build from there. Kick it off at a leisurely 118bpm and bring it up gradually to 122. End with some dancier, poppy, singable stuff. Simple, really.

description:
My favourite event of the year is without question the Frolic Campout. This year, I played on the main night stage 2:45am-4:00am. Bedtime for some, but not at Frolic. The energy from Friday afternoon all the way through Sunday was bright and beautiful and the dance floor was hopping well until the sun came up.

(apologies to the Sheriff who heard the bass from his house)

title: Live at Friends 'n' Family XXI, Saratoga Springs
description:
Friends 'n' Family is so hard to describe. It's a party but it's also a community. It's light and also sound. It's art and also science. It's whimsy and also deep connection. And for all those reasons, it's just a huge honour to be selected to play.

This set is the second of the entire weekend, starting the party off in the pool. I took a slightly different approach and dug up some old old tracks for a journey of house and breaks and back. Enjoy.

title: Institution 003: Johnny Messina
description:
Born and raised in Montreal, Canada, Johnny Messina has been DJing for almost 15 years. His style of progressive techno has been influenced by Hernan Cattaneo, Danny Tenaglia, Guy J, and John Digweed. Messina has toured internationally, alongside Marcelo Vasami, and has played alongside some of the world’s most accomplished DJ’s at Stereo, Montreal.

In May, 2017, Johnny Messina played an incredible set for INSTITUTION and MEMETIC, at the Pyramid Cabaret, in Winnipeg, Canada. This guest mix, INSTITUTION 003, is based on that magical night. Thank you, Johnny!

SoundCloud: @dj_johnny_messina
